definitions.definition: A member of the Mongolic people who ruled Manchuria , then northern China as the Liao , then Central Asia as the Qara Khitais , from the 9th to 13th century C.E.

main_definition: A member of the Mongolic people who ruled Manchuria , then northern China as the Liao , then Central Asia as the Qara Khitais , from the 9th to 13th century C.E.

definitions.definition: The Khitan Empire ; the state or land of the Khitan people.
The extinct Para - Mongolic language spoken by the Khitan people.
